sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant API as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Webhook as KServe Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Controller as KServe Controller<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    participant StorageInit as Storage Initializer<br/>Init Container
    participant S3 as S3/GCS/Azure<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Volume as Shared Volume<br/>emptyDir/PVC
    participant Gateway as Istio Gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant Predictor as Model Server Pod<br/>8080/TCP HTTP

    Note over Client,Predictor: Flow 1: InferenceService Creation and Model Serving

    Client->>API: POST InferenceService CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (kubeconfig)
    API->>Webhook: Validate/Mutate InferenceService<br/>mTLS (API Server)
    Webhook-->>API: Validated/Mutated CR
    API-->>Controller: Watch Event (CR Created)

    Controller->>API: Create Knative Service/Deployment<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    Controller->>API: Create VirtualService/DestinationRule<br/>ServiceAccount Token
    API-->>Controller: Resources Created

    Note over StorageInit,Volume: Pod Initialization Phase
    StorageInit->>S3: GET Model Artifacts<br/>AWS SigV4 / GCP SA / Azure Key
    S3-->>StorageInit: Model Files
    StorageInit->>Volume: Write Model Files<br/>Filesystem (Pod-level isolation)

    Note over Volume,Predictor: Model Server Startup
    Predictor->>Volume: Read Model Files<br/>Filesystem (Pod-level isolation)
    Predictor-->>Predictor: Load Model into Memory

    Note over Client,Predictor: Inference Request Flow
    Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/models/model:predict<br/>HTTPS, Bearer Token/API Key
    Gateway->>Predictor: Forward Request<br/>HTTP (mTLS if Istio enabled)
    Predictor->>Predictor: Run Inference
    Predictor-->>Gateway: Prediction Result (JSON)
    Gateway-->>Client: Response
